E-commerce Full-Stack (Next.js + Express + SQLite + Stripe + Ably)

Quick start
- Copy .env.example to .env and fill values
- npm install
- npm run dev

The SQLite database will be automatically created in the ./data directory on first run.

Key endpoints
- /api/health
- /api/health/db
- /api/products
- /api/checkout/create-payment-intent (POST)
- /api/stripe/webhook (POST, needs Stripe CLI or Render webhook)

Auth
- NextAuth OAuth with Google and GitHub; admin allow-list via ADMIN_EMAILS

Inventory
- Reservation at PaymentIntent creation; release on cancel/failure; capture on success
- Ably channel per variant: inventory:{variantId}, event: 'update', payload: { variantId, available }

Database
- SQLite with better-sqlite3 for simplicity and portability
- Schema automatically initialized on startup

Deploy
- Render via render.yaml and Dockerfile with persistent disk for SQLite database
